013package org.apache.juneau.bean.html5;
014
015/**
016 * Various useful static methods for creating HTML elements.
017 *
018 * <p>
019 * The HtmlBuilder class contains lots of static creator methods to minimize the amount of code needed to produce HTML DOMs.
020 * Instead of using constructors directly, you can use these static methods for more concise code.
021 *
022 * <h5 class='section'>Examples:</h5>
023 * <p class='bcode w800'>
024 *    <jk>import static</jk> org.apache.juneau.bean.html5.HtmlBuilder.*;
025 * 
026 *    <jc>// Instead of this...</jc>
027 *    P <jv>address</jv> = <jk>new</jk> P()
028 *       .children(
029 *          <js>"John Doe"</js>,
030 *          <jk>new</jk> Br(),
031 *          <js>"123 Main Street"</js>,
032 *          <jk>new</jk> Br(),
033 *          <js>"Anytown, ST 12345"</js>
034 *       );
035 * 
036 *    <jc>// ...you can write this...</jc>
037 *    P <jv>address</jv> = <jsm>p</jsm>(
038 *       <js>"John Doe"</js>,
039 *       <jsm>br</jsm>(),
040 *       <js>"123 Main Street"</js>,
041 *       <jsm>br</jsm>(),
042 *       <js>"Anytown, ST 12345"</js>
043 *    );
044 * 
045 *    <jc>// Form with builder methods</jc>
046 *    Form <jv>form</jv> = <jsm>form</jsm>(<js>"/submit"</js>,
047 *       <jsm>input</jsm>(<js>"text"</js>).name(<js>"username"</js>).placeholder(<js>"Username"</js>),
048 *       <jsm>input</jsm>(<js>"password"</js>).name(<js>"password"</js>).placeholder(<js>"Password"</js>),
049 *       <jsm>button</jsm>(<js>"submit"</js>, <js>"Login"</js>)
050 *    );
051 * 
052 *    <jc>// Table with builder methods</jc>
053 *    Table <jv>table</jv> = <jsm>table</jsm>(
054 *       <jsm>thead</jsm>(
055 *          <jsm>tr</jsm>(
056 *             <jsm>th</jsm>(<js>"Name"</js>),
057 *             <jsm>th</jsm>(<js>"Age"</js>),
058 *             <jsm>th</jsm>(<js>"City"</js>)
059 *          )
060 *       ),
061 *       <jsm>tbody</jsm>(
062 *          <jsm>tr</jsm>(
063 *             <jsm>td</jsm>(<js>"John Doe"</js>),
064 *             <jsm>td</jsm>(<js>"25"</js>),
065 *             <jsm>td</jsm>(<js>"New York"</js>)
066 *          ),
067 *          <jsm>tr</jsm>(
068 *             <jsm>td</jsm>(<js>"Jane Smith"</js>),
069 *             <jsm>td</jsm>(<js>"30"</js>),
070 *             <jsm>td</jsm>(<js>"Los Angeles"</js>)
071 *          )
072 *       )
073 *    );
074 * 
075 *    <jc>// Navigation menu</jc>
076 *    Nav <jv>nav</jv> = <jsm>nav</jsm>(
077 *       <jsm>ul</jsm>(
078 *          <jsm>li</jsm>(<jsm>a</jsm>(<js>"/home"</js>, <js>"Home"</js>)),
079 *          <jsm>li</jsm>(<jsm>a</jsm>(<js>"/about"</js>, <js>"About"</js>)),
080 *          <jsm>li</jsm>(<jsm>a</jsm>(<js>"/contact"</js>, <js>"Contact"</js>))
081 *       )
082 *    );
083 * 
084 *    <jc>// Fieldset with attributes after children</jc>
085 *    Fieldset <jv>fieldset</jv> = <jsm>fieldset</jsm>(
086 *       <jsm>legend</jsm>(<js>"User Information"</js>),
087 *       <jsm>input</jsm>(<js>"text"</js>).name(<js>"firstName"</js>).placeholder(<js>"First Name"</js>),
088 *       <jsm>input</jsm>(<js>"text"</js>).name(<js>"lastName"</js>).placeholder(<js>"Last Name"</js>)
089 *    ).disabled(<jk>true</jk>);
090 * 
091 *    <jc>// List with mixed content</jc>
092 *    Ul <jv>list</jv> = <jsm>ul</jsm>(
093 *       <jsm>li</jsm>(<js>"Simple item"</js>),
094 *       <jsm>li</jsm>(<jsm>strong</jsm>(<js>"Bold item"</js>)),
095 *       <jsm>li</jsm>(
096 *          <js>"Item with "</js>,
097 *          <jsm>em</jsm>(<js>"emphasis"</js>),
098 *          <js>" and "</js>,
099 *          <jsm>code</jsm>(<js>"code"</js>)
100 *       )
101 *    );
102 * 
103 *    <jc>// Media elements</jc>
104 *    Video <jv>video</jv> = <jsm>video</jsm>(<js>"/path/to/video.mp4"</js>)
105 *       .controls(<jk>true</jk>)
106 *       .width(640)
107 *       .height(480)
108 *       .children(
109 *          <jsm>track</jsm>(<js>"/path/to/subtitles.vtt"</js>, <js>"captions"</js>).srclang(<js>"en"</js>).label(<js>"English"</js>)
110 *       );
111 * 
112 *    Audio <jv>audio</jv> = <jsm>audio</jsm>(<js>"/path/to/audio.mp3"</js>)
113 *       .controls(<jk>true</jk>)
114 *       .autoplay(<jk>false</jk>)
115 *       .children(
116 *          <jsm>source</jsm>(<js>"/path/to/audio.ogg"</js>, <js>"audio/ogg"</js>),
117 *          <jsm>source</jsm>(<js>"/path/to/audio.mp3"</js>, <js>"audio/mpeg"</js>)
118 *       );
119 * </p>
120 *
121 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
122 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/JuneauBeanHtml5">juneau-bean-html5</a>
123 * </ul>
124 */
125public class HtmlBuilder {
126
127   /**
128    * Constructor.
129    */
130   protected HtmlBuilder() {}
131
132   /**
133    * Creates an empty {@link A} element.
134    *
135    * @return The new element.
136    */
137   public static final A a() {
138      return new A();
139   }
140
141   /**
142    * Creates an {@link A} element with the specified {@link A#href(Object)} attribute and {@link A#children(Object[])}
143    * nodes.
144    *
145    * @param href The {@link A#href(Object)} attribute.
146    * @param children The {@link A#children(Object[])} nodes.
147    * @return The new element.
148    */
149   public static final A a(Object href, Object...children) {
150      return new A(href, children);
151   }
